			<a name="What_is_OpenCATS.3F" id="What_is_OpenCATS.3F"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> What is OpenCATS? </span></h2>

<div class="floatright"><a href="http://www.opencats.org/documentation/File:Workflow.png" class="image" title="Workflow.png"><img alt="" href="http://www.opencats.org/wiki/images/thumb/a/ae/Workflow.png/180px-Workflow.png" width="180" height="119" border="0" /></a></div>OpenCATS is a free <a href="http://www.opencats.orghttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Applicant_tracking_system" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Applicant_tracking_system" rel="nofollow">Applicant Tracking System</a> (ATS).<br />
<p>..designed for Recruiters by the recruiting community who need to manage the recruitment process from job posting, candidate application, through to candidate selection and submission.
</p><p>This free  and open application will install on Linux or Windows to manage your recruiting workflow. 
<br /><br /><br />
</p>
<a name="Thinking_Free_ATS.3F_Think_OpenCATS.21" id="Thinking_Free_ATS.3F_Think_OpenCATS.21"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline"><span style="color:#000080"> Thinking Free ATS? Think OpenCATS! </span></span></h3>
